Hi Unive, thanks for the update. Looking at it again I have some minor comments.
We're decoding the message here, right? :)
Oops, let me fix it. ;)
`s/encode/decode/`
Done
`s/encode/decode/`
Done

This should rather be `-EOVERFLOW`. `-EINVAL` should only be used for arguments directly under the caller's control. The length of the received message is not something that's under the caller's control.

Please audit the rest of the patch for the same.
Done

This can now be reduced to:

```
return pldm_msgbuf_destroy_consumed(buf);
```

Please audit the rest of the patch for the same.
Done, looking around this is the only one for this patch.
Again, `-EOVERFLOW` here.
Done

Ah, so while `-EINVAL` not right, my suggestion for `-EOVERFLOW` could also do with some improvement. We've returned `-EBADMSG` in other decoders for this error. As the message can never have been valid I think that's reasonable.

I've fixed them up myself and I'll push the result in a moment.

This is another instance of being able to do:

```
return pldm_msgbuf_destroy(buf);
```

I'll fix it for you though.
